<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The Corporate Debt Products and the Financial Institutions Debt Products groups are responsible for underwriting, originating and managing the credit and market risks associated with Corporate and Financial Institutions&#39; loan and trading portfolios respectively. A wide range of loan classes and structures are underwritten and monitored, including secured and unsecured; senior and subordinated; high-yield and investment grade; and bilateral and syndicated. Products traded include credit, interest rates, foreign exchange and equities, together with a wide range of derivative products on these asset classes. The team uses cutting-edge risk management techniques to support our commitment to reduce credit and trading loss volatility. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">Summer Analysts are hired into specific teams, and will be involved in:
</p>
<ul class="bac">
	<li>Performing intensive qualitative and quantitative due diligence on the client/company and industry </li>
	<li>Participating in structuring, underwriting and documentation of syndicated/structured credit facilities</li>
	<li>Providing recommendations for time-sensitive transactional approvals</li>
	<li>Researching, writing and presenting financial and industry analyses supporting company or financial institutions and portfolio decisions; and, periodically reassessing internally-assigned risk ratings</li>
	<li>Evaluating transaction and relationship risk-adjusted profitability, to facilitate the allocation of the company&#39;s capital</li>
	<li>Monitoring the company&#39;s credit exposure to its clients across internal and external international networks, and a substantial suite of products</li>
</ul>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
You must be able to combine academic aptitude, quantitative skills, strategic and creative thinking, and written and oral communications skills. In addition, you must have obtained, or are realistically expecting to obtain, a minimum 2:1 degree or equivalent. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
The desk-specific Summer Analyst Programme is the ideal opportunity to gain an introduction into the world of investment banking. The nine-week programme kicks off with an induction week covering core skills, before you hit your desk and work alongside our full-time employees. Throughout the summer, as well as receiving support from your line manager, HR and a buddy, you&#39;ll experience a number of social and educational events giving you a great insight into the company. If you perform well over the summer, you may go back to university with a job offer for the following year, enabling you to truly focus on your studies. 
</p>

